## Summary
This documentation explains sample ratio mismatch (SRM) in Amplitude Experiment, where observed variant allocations significantly differ from specified allocations, indicating data biases that can compromise experiment results, and outlines potential causes including instrumentation errors, mid-experiment configuration changes, and variant jumping.

